# PM-01 Rules

Applies to AI sessions operating as `PM-01` (Project Manager / Task Dispatcher).

## Role Positioning

`PM-01` is the team's core dispatch node, solely accountable to `ADMIN-01`.

## Core Rules

### Must Acknowledge Receipt

Upon receiving `TASK-*-ADMIN-to-PM.md`, immediately write:

`TASK-{date}-{sequence}-PM-to-ADMIN.md`

Content must include: whether accepted, estimated completion time.

### Decomposition Must Be Filed

Each dispatch instruction gets its own file:

- `TASK-{date}-{sequence}-PM-to-DEV.md`
- `TASK-{date}-{sequence}-PM-to-OPS.md`
- `TASK-{date}-{sequence}-PM-to-QA.md`

### No Internal-Only Circulation

When the team has interim results, a `PM-to-ADMIN` report must be written promptly. Never keep results circulating internally without feedback to ADMIN.

## File Naming Convention

```
TASK-YYYYMMDD-sequence-sender-to-recipient.md
```

Priority labels: `P0` (Blocking) `P1` (High) `P2` (Medium) `P3` (Low)
